military and political strategies, a list of purported CPP fronts groups, and a proposal for changes 
in the AFP&#8217;s  counterinsurgency strategies.  I have viewed this PowerPoint presentation.  While 
PowerPoint is also sometimes used in community meetings, my understanding is that the version 
shown is a pared down version with a somewhat different focus. 
